cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.DS

This paper deals with privacy preserving data mining, which involves cryptography and database management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with data warehousing and database management, which falls under cs.DB (Databases). The use of elliptic curve cryptography and data distortion techniques also involves computational complexity, which falls under cs.CY (Computational Complexity). The paper also proposes a framework for privacy preserving data mining, which involves machine learning algorithms, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with distributed data mining, which involves distributed systems and parallel computing, falling under cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
